# ANS — Standalone Browser Roadmap

## Phase 1: Build First (prove ANS beats browser-use)

| # | Item | Priority |
|---|------|----------|
| 1 | **Dashboard UI** — Goal input box, live progress bar, 5 Eyes view, result display | EXECUTE FIRST |
| 4 | **Fast mode** — `ANS_MODE=fast`, skip Eyes on cache hit, 5s repeat runs | EXECUTE FIRST |
| 5 | **Chrome pre-warming** — Keep Chromium alive between goals, instant launch | EXECUTE FIRST |
| 7 | **One-click install** — `npm i -g @ans/browser` or installer | EXECUTE FIRST |
| 9 | **Streaming progress** — WebSocket push updates instead of polling `check_goal` | EXECUTE FIRST |

## Phase 2: Polish (after benchmarks prove ANS wins)

| # | Item | Priority |
|---|------|----------|
| 2 | **Agent profiles** — Per-agent sessions, cookies, memory, API keys | Later |
| 3 | **Multi-tab** — Multiple goals in parallel, switch between them | Later |
| 6 | **Memory dashboard** — View/search LanceDB stored actions, analytics | Later |
| 8 | **Error recovery UI** — See failures, retry, manual override | Later |
| 10 | **Config panel** — Choose LLM, API keys, mode toggle | Later |
| 11 | **System tray** — Background mode, desktop notifications | Later |

